UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1475
1 WHEREAS, Bob DeWeese was a member of the Rotary Club of Louisville and the
2 University of Kentucky Alumni Association. He served on the University of Louisville
3 Board of Overseers and the UofL Cancer Board, and was an avid supporter of The
4 Healing Place; and
5 WHEREAS, Bob DeWeese was a faithful servant of God, and for many years he
6 and his beloved wife, Angie, were members of Christ Church United Methodist; and
7 WHEREAS, Bob DeWeese proudly showed his love for the Commonwealth and
8 America by always displaying both flags; and
9 WHEREAS, Bob DeWeese loved the outdoors, was a avid gardener, enjoyed golf,
10 and, most importantly, treasured spending time with his children and grandchildren; and
11 WHEREAS, Bobby "Bob" Miller DeWeese, renowned Kentucky physician;
12 esteemed former member of the Kentucky House of Representatives; and cherished
13 husband, father, and grandfather, departed this earthly life and entered into the Kingdom
14 of Heaven on November 25, 2020, leaving all those whose lives he touched in solemn
15 mourning; and
16 WHEREAS, whether in the role of doctor, legislator, or volunteer, the extraordinary
17 life and legacy of public service exemplified by Representative Bob DeWeese is worthy
18 of tangible public recognition;
19 NOW, THEREFORE,
20 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
21 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate the portion of United
22 States Route 42 in Jefferson County, from its intersection with Mockingbird Valley Road
23 at mile point 3.279 to the Jefferson/Oldham County line, as the "Representative Bob
24 DeWeese Memorial Highway" and shall, within 30 days of the effective date of this
25 Resolution, erect appropriate signage denoting this designation. This designation shall
26 supersede any previous honorary designation for this section of highway.
